species.name: Neimoidian
species.description: Neimoidians closely resemble their Duros cousins. Both species are smooth-skinned hairless humanoids with large red eyes and blue-freen skin, and both species hatch from eggs in a larval "grub" stage. A closer look reveals more gray tones in Neimoidian skin. Additoinally, Neimoidians' pupils split horizontally, and their distinct skeletal structure creates protrusions on their foreheads.
species.startSkills: Begin with 1 rank in either Deception or Negotiation
